sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1319017
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part is combined from other parts
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device produces iLOV (K660004) in response to a quorum sensing input.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There's another scar between C0179 and B0015 that should not affect the functionality.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Arne Zimmermann, Michael Osthege

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the sequence of the SpeI/XbaI scar for RBS-CDS junctions in BioBricks standard assembly.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is a shorter scar to ensure proper spacing between the RBS and CDS.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SX scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: XbaI/SpeI mixed site. Simply used to aid in entry of parts into the registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J64010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Promoter driving the lasI gene in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
Activated by LasR+3OC12HSL and not RhlR+C4HSL (Seed et al., 1995)
~4x stronger than the lasB promoter (BBa_R0079; Seed et al., 1995).
Switch point ~0.1nM 3OC12HSL (Seed et al., 1995)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Promoter sequence cropped to 4nt upstream of Las box according to example of Whiteley and Greenberg, J. Bac, 2001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jeffrey J Tabor

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K660004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: iLOV is a version of LOV2 that has been altered through site directed mutagenesis and DNA shuffling.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: iLOV has the same function and uses as LOV2. As a reporter, it is advantageous over GFP derived fluorescent proteins due to its small size (useful if you are tagging proteins), ability to recover quickly from photobleaching and use in anoxic conditions.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: illegal restriction sites. The part was synthesized to remove them.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Glasgow Uni 2011

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lasR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: lasR activator from P. aeruginosa PAO1(no LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: same as C0079 except no LVA tag
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jcbraff

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
